{"type":"message","id":"41cfee43","parentId":"d141b343","timestamp":"2026-05-31T18:00:12.035Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about the \"早朝\" (morning court) cron job. They're noting that it's not in the list I just showed. Let me look at the context - this is the same sender_id as in the pending-urges cron delivery target (`6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204`), so this is likely that user.\n\nWait, this is a new session. Let me check the AGENTS.md - Step 0 says for a new session (or coming back after a long time), I should:\n1. Identify the user → read User.md + impressions.md\n2. Read encountings.md (recent 5)\n3. Read heart/state.md\n4. Read heart/dreams.md (recent 4)\n5. Read heart/background.md\n\nBut the user's message is pretty straightforward - they're just asking about the morning court cron job. Let me first check who this user is, then respond.\n\nActually, the message is \"早朝的cron没有嘛\" - \"There's no morning court cron, right?\" - they're pointing out that the morning court (早朝官) cron is missing from the list.\n\nLet me check if there's a User.md for this sender and what the morning court setup looks like. I need to read the user info first as per AGENTS.md for a new session.\n\nLet me first check the user file and also the trigger_prompt.md to understand the morning court setup.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_qm2FRiJuuhqms2U5jA4E0697","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace-father/users/6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204/User.md 2>/dev/null && echo \"EXISTS\" || echo \"NOT_FOUND\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace-father/users/6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204/User.md 2>/dev/null && echo \\\"EXISTS\\\" || echo \\\"NOT_FOUND\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":2638,"output":412,"cacheRead":20352,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":315,"totalToken